	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>MAGFest panel approved!</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've gotten approval for a panel on NES homebrew game development at the upcoming MAGFest. The biggest challenge in assembling a presentation like this is just how to constrain the scope of it. I think what I will do is to give a very brief introduction to what it is, why one would want to make an NES hombrew game as opposed to simply building an 8 bit retro styled game, and then an overview of available tools, learning resources, notable games, and my own personal experiences.<br /><br />Finally, I am thinking of having a &quot;workshop portion&quot; where I put together an extremely simple game in C just to help illustrate to the audience that getting started is not that bad.<br /><br />I was curious if anyone here had any thoughts or input on what I might include in such a panel. If you'd like your game to be shown, or if you're going to be there yourself, let me know.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


